DE TIPS voor de wintermaanden.... 4 nachten, 5 dagen disney
Wij zijn met 5 kids en 2 volwassenen gegaan (2 huisjes)
Bij aankomst word je aan de poort opgewacht. je hebt alleen je boekingsnummer nodig om voor de 1e keer door de poort te gaan. je kan je gewoon op elke tijdstip inchecken zodat je vroeg naar het disney park kan gaan. (receptie is niet te missen je rijd er zo heen)
personeel is heel behulpzaam en vriendelijk (spreken geen Nederlands)
Huisjes zijn redelijk schoon maar bestek/servies/pannen/koelkast kan je het beste zelf even afwassen want dat is gewoon niet schoon. verder heb je meerdere verwarmingen, airco, tv met een paar zenders, 2x wc/douche, vaatwasser, magnetron, elektrische kookplaat, koffiezetapparaat, waterkoker, tafel met 6 stoelen, bank en een kluisje.
De kast opbergruimte in de 2 persoons slaapkamer is ruim voldoende maar voor de andere kamer heb je net genoeg opbergruimte voor 2 personen. in deze 2e kamer kunnen wel 3 personen makkelijk slapen. Een 4e erbij dan moet je een uitschuif bed pakken dat word best krap slapen denk ik. (niet nodig gehad)
Losse spulletjes in de huisjes:
6x borden, bekers, mokken, schaaltjes, messen, vorken, lepels, theelepels, 1 koekenpan, 1 kookpan, grote schaal, kledingrek, bezem+blik, kleine flesjes shampoo, 2 zeepjes, 2 handdoeken per badkamer, broodmes voor stokbrood, 1x pannenonderzetter, 1x wcrol per wc. kan zijn dat ik nog wat vergeten ben maar dit was wel het hoognodige.
Wij hebben geen gebruik gemaakt van het zwembad en buiten picknick/bbq.
TIPS voor het huisje.
Persoonlijk zou ik vers brood van de bakker meenemen zodat je de 1e dagen heel vroeg in disney kan zijn. het brood wat je hier koopt is anders (steviger) en smiddags ligt er alleen nog wat droog brood in de winkel. ook Beleg zoals pindakaas/hagelslag etc zou ik al meenemen. calve pindakaas kennen ze denk ik niet. eigenlijk komt het erop neer dat je beter een boodschappen tas vol naar je huisje mee kan nemen als je gewend ben om van 1 smaak te eten -) ook omdat de prijzen duurder zijn dan in Nederland.
De 1e dag is altijd rommelig je wilt naar disney moet nog uitpakken smiddags doodmoe terug dus dan is het raadzaam om na de 1e dag disney lekker makkelijk te eten zonder teveel poespas. soep in de pan of worstjes is een ideale oplossing -).
Vergeet niet om eerst je servies/borden/bestek/pannen eerst te wassen die zijn vies.
neem dus wat mee om de vaat handmatig te doen en te drogen (vergeet vaatdoekje niet)
vaatwasser heeft geen vaatwasser tabletten dus neem deze mee!
owja en de vaatwasser niet aanzetten als je gaat slapen want die maak herrie!
heb je veel opladers/ elektrische apparaten neem een stekkerdoos mee -)
Het water moet je niet drinken uit de kraan ivm Chloor. je ruikt het al als je de kraan openzet.
ook niet gekookt dus koop 5 liter flessen bij auchan in het winkelcentrum val d'europe voor 0,89ct deze winkel is MEGA groot. op de 1e verdieping (entree) kan je van alles kopen maar een verdieping lager zit de supermarkt.

An option for bigger families but in desperate need of an update.
The cabins sleep up to six but are getting dilapidated now.
There are a few key issues . First is the lack of sockets. There is not a SINGLE plug in the main bedroom. Good luck trying to charge your phone. We have to bring multiple extension leads that trail through from the living room.
That main room is lit by just two bare bulbs and so at night is dingy and dark. Forget trying to have any light to cook by! Speaking of which the lack of an oven makes self catering quite limited, despite having a full size fridge freezer and dishwasher!
Cleanliness isn't great. Our bathroom sink was blocked and smelled bad, the toaster only worked if you held down the handle and the whole cabin smelled musty.

Given it now costs twice what we used to pay to stay here five years ago I think that without a major update we would look to try non Disney accommodation in future, which really this already feels like. Not what you expect from Disney.

We stayed here as a family of six.
Collecting park tickets on the first morning was effortless. The staff were really well organised and friendly. There was no queue so it only took a couple of minutes to get our park passes and photo pass.
When we returned later in the day, collecting lodge keys was again very organised and efficient.
As per other reviews, the lodges are not new, but ours was immaculately clean, all beds made up and the layout in the woods is amazing. Although they are not huge, we had plenty of space for 6 of us. It has hearing and air con.
The kitchenette is well stocked with Pans, utensils, dishes, cups and glasses. Just keep in mind that there is not an oven, but we just planned accordingly and also used a disposable bbq on the stand outside.
If you are going in a colder month, don't forget to turn the radiators up, we also used the air con fan to circulate the heat better.
The main centre of the park is a lovely space. The shop sells groceries which are reasonably priced and also sells some disney merchandise.
We used the swimming pool which was immaculate and modern. Other reviews have said the water is freezing but we didn't find that to be the case. Lockers are code operated so no need for coins. We went at 3pm and were one of only 2 families there at the time but it got busy at 4pm.
As with all the roads from Calais, the drive into the park only takes a few minutes and is easy to navigate, it's basically a straight road between the two.

Na eten ging een deel van de familie zwemmen.
Zwembad:
Zeer slechte ervaring! Vloer van de kleedhokjes smerig. Vervolgens was het water van het zwembad veel te koud! Aangezien je voor je verblijf flink betaald verwacht je dat dit op orde is! De hele godganse tijd hoor je gefluit van hysterische badmeesters die over ijverig alles in toom proberen te houden. Na een uurtje dobberen wilden we nog in het bubbelbad. Deze is iets warmer van temperatuur, maar nog steeds te koud. Echter na 15 minuten nog geen bubbels. Wij zaten met een dochter van 4 jaar. Gewoon rustig te wachten tot de machine aan zou gaan. Dochter zat gewoon rustig bij ons op schoot, ook al moe en rozig. Kwam een badmeester geÃ¯rriteerd meldden dat kinderen onder de 12 jaar niet in het bubbelbad mogen. Is beleid. Terwijl daar voor nergens een bordje staat bij het bubbelbad. Wij ons van geen kwaad bewust. Mn dochter zat gewoon rustig op schoot (en ze moeten sowieso blij zijn dat kinderen rustig blijven als ze zo lang moeten wachten voordat het start!). Hij vertelde dat kinderen te druk doen in het bubbelbad. Is beleid. Wij gewoon maar het bad uit gegaan. Je wil ook geen scene maken voor anderen. Wat is dit voor leeftijdsdiscriminatie? Er wordt niet geselecteerd op gedrag, maar op leeftijd. Wij moesten als enige familie het bubbelbad uit, alsof we een criminelen waren. Zo voelde het. Mijn dochter had zin in het bubbeldbad voor het slapen, en had in de gaten dat het vanwege haar aanwezigheid kwam, door non-verbale communicatie en wijzen. Ze begon toen we er uit stapten te huilen en vroeg 'wat doe ik dan verkeerd?'. We moesten achteraf uitleggen dat het niet aan haar lag. Geen leuke ervaring om zo je vakantie te beginnen bij Disneyland! Kind onvriendelijke attitude! Terwijl...je zit op Davy Crocket....NIET een of ander luxe hotel. Dit zou juist voor families moeten zijn. Dan mag je toch verwachten dat er spelende kinderen zijn in het zwembad. En mensen die daar niet tegen kunnen, zouden die wel naar davy crocket gaan?
Al met al. Erg negatieve ervaring. Beneden niveau!

Je kunt niet ene huisje iets eerder, omdat dan aantal personen niet duidelijk is. Moeten ze dan helemaal uitzoeken. Want ene huisje zat een persoon minder dan andere huisje. Moest helemaal uitgezocht worden. Probleem ontstaan bij de receptie die indeling van de huisjes anders in systeem had dan wij zelf de verdeling hadden gemaakt. We recently went to Disneyland Paris (8th April 2022) and whilst we enjoyed our time in the Parks the accommodation at the Davy Crocket Ranch was very disappointing. We booked a premium cabin in the Davy Crocket ranch. The cabin was dirty and dilapidated. Whenever we entered the cabin the smell was the first thing we noticed, it smelled like it hadn't been cleaned or aired in a long time. Funky and musty smelling, which is surprising considering Covid19 is still very much in evidence. In the room with the single beds there was a large cobweb between the floor and the false boxed in aperture, this was clearly old and had collected a lot of dust. I had to ask my partner to clean this before my daughter saw it as it would have scared her. We arrived very late due to the travel disruptions, our journey taking more than double the time it would during normal circumstances. We were eager to get some rest, however, when I plugged my phone charging cable into the socket in the main bedroom the wire came back covered in dust and debris. The whole cabin was very tired looking and had clearly seen much better days. The RCD box had at some point been taped closed but this tape was so old it had stopped working so the box hung open with the tape hanging off. Holes in the faux wood walls had been covered over with stickers and the curtains were threadbare and had holes in them, general condition and cleanliness of the cabin were very poor. The beds are extremely noisy, even our young daughter who weighs no more than 5 stone could be heard from the other side of the cabin every time moved. We paid Â£936.53 for two nights and access to the parks and we feel this is awful value for money. Whilst we would return to the parks we would never stay in a Disney owned accommodation again. A shame that the care and attention given to the parks are not reflected in these cabins.

Been going to Disneyland Paris for 15 years, been to Davy Crockett 6 times over those years. Disney? Love it.. Davy Crockett? Looking a little tired.
Pros - It's Disney! The staff are amazing, always willing to help and really go out of their way to do whatever they can to do what is needed. The privacy of the place is something we always like, and of course it is the cheaper option if you are on a budget or have a large family like we do.
The cabins are always spotless and they are large cabins easily sleep 5 adults and you don't get under each other feet, get the bigger cabins and you get 2 shower rooms and toilets, so, no waiting to get ready. The kitchen area is very well stocked and it is easy to cook if you want to save a few pennies. We did quite a nice spread.
The shop is well stocked with the basics, sugar, milk bread, etc, and the breakfast albeit basic has plenty of food, there's always spare.
The restaurant is busy, but the food is excellent, it's a Tex-Mex eat all you want, and has a huge variety of food, we had a fussy eater with us and they had no problems finding something they liked.
The bar is just so nice, the prices are typical Disney but cheaper than some of the other hotels and the service is fantastic, we were looked after so well during our stay.
The pool is huge and clean never really seems crowded.
Cons - The Drive to the parks each morning can be a bit of a drag, although it is a very easy drive, and if you're not there at stupid o'clock then you're normally in row D or E and then you have a very long walk before you've even got to the security gates.
The cabins are starting to look a little tired, several hooks fell off the wall when we hung up our cloths and the pressure in the showers was better last time, they are not dirty, just shabby and need a refresh. The decking was very soft underfoot and felt like it was going to break every now and then.
I would rather have an oven in the cabin than a dishwasher.
Top bungalow,  organisation au top.

For the price Vs any other Disney hotel, this place is fantastic. Set away from the hustle and bustle of general Disney madness, Davy Crockett offers a quieter retreat for those with younger families, or even just those wanting to save a little money.
The place itself is nicely laid out with lodges separated into little areas, each with it's own breakfast shack if you have the breakfast option. The breakfast itself it more than enough to feed you for breakfast and make a sandwich out of the bread for lunch.
The lodges consist of a living area with a large fridge freezer, hob, coffee maker, kettle, toaster and depending on your lodge type even a dish washer or over I believe. There are sets of cutlery and crockery for 6, the maximum in each cabin. There are also a few basic cooking tools such as frying pans, knives, chopping board, saucepan and can opener. However I would suggest bringing your own can opener and a few more tools if you intend to cook a lot and defenitely a drying up towel as we did not have one.
Then there's a separate main bedroom with a double bed and private toilet/shower room. This has plenty of storage space.
The separate room made up of single beds could be a bit of a squeeze with 6 larger adults, but with 5 adults in it was fine.
The beds themselves are not the largest or softest, but luckily Disney days make you exhausted and it doesn't matter too much.
The main area has a separate shower and separate toilet room so showering/loo using can happen independently. Great if you've got a long shower user! The towels provided are as usual tiny, so might be worth packing some if you want big fluffy towels! Bring extra toilet rolls however if you're staying for a long stay as these are not replenished. Soap and shampoo are provided.
We found the lodge covered all out basic needs as were were out for long days, and I would definitely recommend for separate rooms meaning people can stay up late/get up early without waking everyone.
The swimming pool facilities are good for a rest bite though we didn't actually have time to go in the pool!
The restaurant on site offers a great selection of buffet food, similar to that of Cheyenne and Santa Fe, but with a smaller seating area so booking is recommended!
The onsite shop offers the standard Disney merchandise plus plenty of food and lodge essentials such as bread, frozen meals, fruit and vegetables, coffee, milk, toilet and kitchen roll plus more, so going to a large super market isn't necessary.
Other than the lodges seeming a little dated , which is the main issue people may have, and being a little dark around the walkways at night, I thoroughly enjoyed my stay here and thought it was a great break from the hectic Disney life in the Disney bubble.

Good location about a 10 mins drive to the parks. This also means you do not need to eat in the parks. The food at the hotel doesn't even deserve 1 star it is extortionate and inedible. We paid 102 euros for 2 adults and 1 child for 3 all you can eat buffet and 1 large and 1 small beer. You get given a small plate. We probably didn't eat one plate between the 3 of us. The ribs were grey the rest was over cooked and just awful. We don't mind paying the price if the food is a good standard but this was awful. You wouldn't feed it to your dog.
We ate out the following 2 nights for half the price and much better quality food.
The actually accommodation was fine. Double room is slightly small but enough room for 2. The room with several beds in is of a good size. It's great that there are 2 bathrooms. There is a hairdryer too.
However there is no grill or oven if you plan on cooking whilst there
Neither are there any tea towels.
The TV is meant to have several english speaking channels. We only had one ( even though we pressed the flag that should have changed the language to english) Funnily enough the only one in English was the one talking about the parks.
We were quite close to reception so our internet service as good. We watched Netflix with no problems.
They do not leave any cleaning products to wash your pots. You need to go to the outpost and ask for the free cleaning pack. Which has a miniature bottle of fairy liquid in and 2 dishwasher tablets. Surely this would make more sense to leave in each cabin on check in ?
Tennis court is a good option and it is free to hire tennis racquets and balls so no need to take these with you.
Pool is a good size but it is cold!
You are about 10 mins drive to Val De Europe shopping area where there is a supermarket and several restaurants.
On the whole would i return possibly although i think i would be inclined to look at next door the Village Nature.
